## Session Completion (MANDATORY)

Every working session MUST persist state before ending. Skipping these
steps causes knowledge loss across sessions:

1. Write session memory to `{{DOCS_MEMORY}}/` — include task IDs completed, files modified, decisions, failed approaches, and next steps
2. Capture compound learnings via the compound skill when hard-won solutions were discovered
3. Refresh or mark stale compound learnings when shipped work invalidates existing guidance in `{{DOCS_COMPOUND}}/`
4. Invoke **compact-context** when tracking files exceed the configured threshold
5. Run quality gates (if code changed)
6. Update work item status via backlog tools
7. Push to remote (MANDATORY)
8. Provide handoff context for next session

